---

# Introduction

Selection controls allow users to:

* Select one option
* Select multiple options
* Choose from a list
* Pick a date
* Store hidden values

These controls are commonly used in registration forms, employee portals, and data entry screens.

---

# 1. CheckBox

## Definition

A **CheckBox** allows the user to select or deselect an option.

Unlike RadioButton, multiple CheckBoxes can be selected.

---

## Syntax

```aspx
<asp:CheckBox
    ID="chkTerms"
    runat="server"
    Text="I Accept Terms & Conditions" />
```

---

## Important Properties

| Property     | Purpose                            |
| ------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| Text         | Text displayed beside CheckBox     |
| Checked      | Returns True or False              |
| AutoPostBack | Automatically posts page to server |

---

## Code Behind

```csharp
if (chkTerms.Checked)
{
    lblResult.Text = "Accepted";
}
else
{
    lblResult.Text = "Please accept terms.";
}
```

---

## Output

If checked:

```text
Accepted
```

If unchecked:

```text
Please accept terms.
```

---

## Company Usage

* Accept Terms
* Remember Me
* Enable Notifications
* User Permissions

---

# 2. RadioButton

## Definition

A **RadioButton** allows the user to select only **one option** from a group.

---

## Syntax

```aspx
<asp:RadioButton
    ID="rbMale"
    runat="server"
    GroupName="Gender"
    Text="Male" />

<asp:RadioButton
    ID="rbFemale"
    runat="server"
    GroupName="Gender"
    Text="Female" />
```

---

## Code Behind

```csharp
if (rbMale.Checked)
{
    lblGender.Text = "Male";
}
else if (rbFemale.Checked)
{
    lblGender.Text = "Female";
}
```

---

## Output

```text
Male
```

or

```text
Female
```

---

## Company Usage

* Gender
* Payment Method
* Active / Inactive
* Yes / No

---

# CheckBox vs RadioButton

| CheckBox              | RadioButton           |
| --------------------- | --------------------- |
| Multiple selections   | Single selection      |
| Independent           | Group-based           |
| Uses Checked property | Uses Checked property |

---

# 3. DropDownList

## Definition

A **DropDownList** displays a list of options where the user can select one value.

---

## Syntax

```aspx
<asp:DropDownList
    ID="ddlCity"
    runat="server">

    <asp:ListItem>Pune</asp:ListItem>
    <asp:ListItem>Mumbai</asp:ListItem>
    <asp:ListItem>Kolhapur</asp:ListItem>

</asp:DropDownList>
```

---

## Reading Selected Value

```csharp
lblCity.Text = ddlCity.SelectedItem.Text;
```

or

```csharp
string city = ddlCity.SelectedValue;
```

---

## Output

```text
Pune
```

---

## AutoPostBack Example

```aspx
AutoPostBack="true"
OnSelectedIndexChanged="ddlCity_SelectedIndexChanged"
```

```csharp
protected void ddlCity_SelectedIndexChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    lblCity.Text = ddlCity.SelectedValue;
}
```

---

## Company Usage

* Department
* Country
* State
* City
* Designation

---

# 4. ListBox

## Definition

A **ListBox** displays multiple items and can allow single or multiple selection.

---

## Syntax

```aspx
<asp:ListBox
    ID="lstSkills"
    runat="server"
    SelectionMode="Multiple">

    <asp:ListItem>C#</asp:ListItem>
    <asp:ListItem>SQL</asp:ListItem>
    <asp:ListItem>ASP.NET</asp:ListItem>

</asp:ListBox>
```

---

## Reading Selected Items

```csharp
foreach (ListItem item in lstSkills.Items)
{
    if (item.Selected)
    {
        lblSkills.Text += item.Text + " ";
    }
}
```

---

## Output

```text
C# SQL
```

---

## Company Usage

* Employee Skills
* User Roles
* Available Modules
* Multiple Permissions

---

# DropDownList vs ListBox

| DropDownList     | ListBox                      |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------- |
| One visible item | Multiple visible items       |
| Single selection | Single or multiple selection |
| Saves space      | Better for multiple choices  |

---

# 5. HiddenField

## Definition

A **HiddenField** stores data on the page that is not visible to the user.

---

## Why Use HiddenField?

Sometimes we need to store information such as:

* Employee ID
* User ID
* Product ID
* Record ID

without displaying it.

---

## Syntax

```aspx
<asp:HiddenField
    ID="hfEmployeeId"
    runat="server"
    Value="101" />
```

---

## Reading Value

```csharp
string id = hfEmployeeId.Value;
```

---

## Output

```text
101
```

(User cannot see it on the page.)

---

## Company Usage

* Store Record IDs
* Store User IDs
* Store Product IDs
* Store Temporary Values

---

# 6. Calendar

## Definition

The **Calendar** control allows users to select a date from a calendar interface.

---

## Syntax

```aspx
<asp:Calendar
    ID="calDOB"
    runat="server" />
```

---

## Reading Selected Date

```csharp
lblDate.Text =
calDOB.SelectedDate.ToShortDateString();
```

---

## Output

```text
22/07/2026
```

---

## SelectedDateChanged Event

```aspx
<asp:Calendar
    ID="calDOB"
    runat="server"
    OnSelectionChanged="calDOB_SelectionChanged" />
```

```csharp
protected void calDOB_SelectionChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    lblDate.Text =
    calDOB.SelectedDate.ToShortDateString();
}
```

---

## Company Usage

* Date of Birth
* Joining Date
* Leave Request
* Booking Date

---

# Summary of Selection Controls

| Control      | Purpose                         |
| ------------ | ------------------------------- |
| CheckBox     | Multiple independent selections |
| RadioButton  | Single selection from a group   |
| DropDownList | Select one item from a list     |
| ListBox      | Single or multiple selections   |
| HiddenField  | Store hidden values             |
| Calendar     | Select dates                    |

